# Planlet UI preferences

Keep Planlet aligned with these design principles:

- **Minimal, reductive, clean** — remove before adding; clarity over feature density
- **Mobile-first** — thumb-friendly spacing, compact layouts, conventional interactions
- **Progressive disclosure** — show less by default; reveal detail on demand
- **No visual noise** — no raw URLs, debug output, filenames, or internal metadata in main UI
- **Restrained metadata** — avoid too many chips or controls on list/card surfaces
- **Short previews** — prefer truncated excerpts and “Show more” over long inline text
- **Scannable lists, calm details** — list pages should scan fast; detail pages can be richer but still readable

## Life Lab

When improving Life Lab, prioritize **clarity and readability** over adding visible features.

List pages: compact cards, filtered previews, capped chips, grouped “Show more”.
Detail pages: structured content and progressive sections; keep the default view calm.

Match existing patterns in `components/life-lab/` and `lib/life-lab/card-preview.ts`.
